festival.introText:
Pack your ponchos... it's time to head OUT EAST!
 
A music & creative festival for open-minded folk, families & friends.
 
Featuring eight different music stages and areas including cabaret tent, spoken word & comedy tent, huge food canteen & beer village, workshops, healing and chill spaces, dedicated kids zone, plus creative trails and installations galore!

faqs.question: Where is Out East Festival?
faqs.answer: Out East Festival is located within the grounds surrounding the neoclassical country house - Dalkeith Country Park.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

Refunds can only be offered if the event is canceled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Im disabled, what help is there?
faqs.answer:
We always aim to provide the best experience for everyone and strive to constantly improve.  

 

Personal assistant - pa 

Their ticket is provided on the expectation that they are willing and able to assist you, throughout your visit and in the event of an evacuation they are your main point of assistance. 

Crowd management personnel located near the viewing platform will assist in moving everybody to a place of safety. 

 

Pa tickets will not be posted out and will be available only on the day for collection

To qualify for the free carer/pa ticket, it is mandatory to provide one of the following forms of supporting documentation as evidence of your requirements along with your ticket order confirmation number: 

- PIP (Personal independence payment) 

- DLA – care and/or mobility 

- D/deaf or blind registration 

- The Access Card or equivalent with a +1 Icon for PA tickets 

- Blue Badge – permitted for parking only requests 

 

Please note, the name on the purchased festival ticket must match the name on the evidence of entitlement provided in order for a free carer pass to be granted. 

 

BEFORE BOOKING 

Please note Out East Festival is largely a green-field site, with some tarmac paths on the entrances and exits. 

While there are some sheltered areas, it is mainly an open-air event, Ground conditions are therefore weather dependent, therefore mobility across the site may become compromised. We ask you to consider this before booking a ticket. 

 

COMPANION TICKET SCHEME 

We operate a companion ticket scheme, at no extra cost, for eligible customers, available only on Adult and Teen Tickets. These can be applied for when booking. 

 

How To Book  

If you know you’ll be applying for a companion ticket then please do not book a ticket for them at your initial booking, as this will not be refunded if your application is approved. 

Book the required number of festival tickets you need, minus companion. 

Apply for your companion ticket and submit supporting documentation using our Accessibility Application Form. Please got to https://www.outeastfest.co.uk/accessibility to apply.

Applications will close on Monday 5th July 2022, unless sold out earlier. 

 

ACCESSIBLE CAR PARKING 

Only one car is permitted per party for the registered accessibility festival goer in the Accessibility Car Park. Blue badge parking spaces can be booked on our access form,

Any other vehicles must be parked in the General Car Park. 

 

ACCESSIBLE DROP OFF 

If you’re being dropped off at the festival, there’s a drop off / pick up point within close proximity to the Accessibility Check-In Point. 

From the drop-off point to the Main Arena is approximately 200m over a gravel pathway and green-field site. 

 

ACCESSIBLE FACILITIES 

Viewing platform at Main Stage (unsheltered) 

Wheelchair-accessible loos at viewing platform and each of the main toilet blocks throughout the arena. 

Induction loops will be available from the Accessibility Check-In Point upon arrival. 

Medical Tent with trained First Aiders. 

Electric wheelchair charging point located at the viewing platform 

Assistance dog resting area located at the Welfare tent. 

Lowered bars, which will also have large-print men- us. 

Refrigerated storage of medication if necessary. 

 

ASSISTANCE DOGS 

While we cannot allow pets of any kind into the festival, registered assistance dogs are permitted. 

If you plan on bringing an assistance dog, please let us know in advance via the Accessibility Application Form so that we are adequately prepared for this. 

Otherwise, we cannot guarantee entry of the assistance dog. 

 

DEAF & HARD OF HEARING CUSTOMERS 

A Sign Language Interpreting Services will at Out East Festival Friday and Saturday providing BSL Interpreting services. 

If this is a service you require please fill out our Accessibility Application Form so you can make the most of these services. We’d like to know your suggestions on what we have interpreted, please send all suggestions to accessibility@outeastfest.co.uk 

 

TICKET ARRIVAL 

Your wristbands and any applicable accessibility passes will be available to collect from the Accessibility Check-In Point on arrival. 

Please ensure you have your confirmation email or mobile ticket ready to collect these.

For any further questions regarding accessibility at Out East Festival, please contact us via accessibility@outeastfest.co.uk

faqs.question: Does Out East Festival have onsite camping?
faqs.answer:
Yes, Out East Festival has camping areas available for tent pitching. The festival also accommodates for live-in vehicles and electrical hookups.

 

Camping Tickets on sale soon.

faqs.question: When is Out East Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: Out East takes place on Saturday 5th and Sunday 6th August 2023.

faqs.question: Does Out East Festival have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: No, there are no age restrictions at Out East Festival, any ages are welcome.
